package a59Inner_classes_Part1;

public class aSample {
	
	/*
	 * nested type class anna inner class ana rendu vakatea.
	 * asal nduku e inner classes aneadi introduce cheasaru antea scope aneadi limited ga ravatam 
	   kosam, and adana classes loni members ni accesschaiyali antea by using inheritance concept
	   kani accessbility modifers public, private, protected, default vitini base cheasukonea
	   adina nuvu access cheasuko galutavu.
	   least access una modifier adi antea private. private untea inner class lonea nuvu access 
	   cheasukogalavu outside of class nuvu access cheasukoleavu. 
	   vaka veala vaka java file chala inner classesunai anuko main class ki private untea danilo
	   members ni aa inner classe lo easy ga access cheasukovachu adea inner classes yoka 
	   speciality.
	   
	   Simple ga chepali antea encapsulation and inheritance concepts inka baga extordinory ga
	   vadukovachu. edi kada inka anonymous classes ni ekada inka baga use cheasukovachu.
	  */
	
	/*
	 1. Can we have more than one class in java file?
	 * Yes, please refer to bTestClass1.java
	 
	 2. Can we have more than one public class in java file?
	 * No, please refer to cTestClass2.java
	 * mana ki java file lo only one public class a untundi adi kuda java filename tho untundi.
	 
	 3. How many class files will be generated when multiple classes are present in java file?
	 * manaki vaka java file lo ani classes untea ani class files generate aavutai.
	 
	 4. Can we have main method in all the classes present at root level of java file?
	 * Yes, but execution time lo matram vakatea class a run aavutadi adikuda manam echina or
	   select cheasina class a run aavutadi.
	   
	 5. if a java class contain more than one class are they considerd as inner class?
	 * These are nott considerd as inner classes.
	 */
	
	/*
	 1. What is Inner class?
	 * vaka class lo inko class member ga untea dani Inner class antamu.
	 
	 2. How many types of Inner classes are there? what are they? 
	 * In java there are four or 4 types of inner classes are there :
	   1. non-static inner classes
	   2. static inner classes
	   1&2 are nested classes
	   3. local classes
	   4. anonymous inner classes/ anonymous classes
	    
	 3. Can we have more than one class in java file?
	 * Yes, please refer to fTestClass5.java but classes names are unique. 
	 * manam vaka veala inner classes ki em access modifier evakapotea java nea default ga default
	   access modifier set chestundi.
	 */

